[4] France: confirmed
Date: Tue 24 May 2022 01:01 CET
Source: France 24 [in French, translated, abridged, edited]
https://www.france24.com/fr/france/20220523-variole-du-singe-trois-cas-d-infection-confirm%C3%A9s-en-france


The spread of monkeypox also affects France. So far in the country, 3 confirmed cases of the disease have been reported Public Health France (SPF) said Monday, 23 May [2022], in a statement.

Confirmed or suspected cases of monkeypox have been identified in several European countries -- United Kingdom, Portugal, Spain, Italy, Belgium, Germany, Sweden, Denmark -- as well as in Australia, Canada and the United States -- a "unusual" spread according to experts.

There are currently "less than 200 confirmed and suspected cases" in non-endemic countries, said Dr. Maria Van Kerkhove, in charge of the fight against COVID-19 at the World Health Organization but also emerging diseases and zoonoses, on Monday [23 May 2022].

