[7] Denmark ex Spain
Date: Mon 23 May 2022 07:30 EDT
Source: Reuters [edited]
https://www.reuters.com/world/europe/denmark-registers-first-case-monkeypox-infection-health-ministry-2022-05-23/


Denmark has registered its 1st incidence of infection with monkeypox in an adult male who had returned from a trip to Spain, the health ministry said in a statement on Monday [23 May 2022].

"Health authorities do not expect widespread infection in Denmark, but we are following the situation closely to be prepared for a possible development in the infection situation," Health Minister Magnus Heunicke said in a statement.

The man is currently in isolation and authorities are in touch with any close contacts, the ministry said.

[Byline: Nikolaj Skydsgaard]

