[9] United Arab Emirates ex West Africa
Date: Tue 24 May 2022
Source: Trade Arabia [edited]
http://www.tradearabia.com/news/HEAL_396700.html


The United Arab Emirates (UAE) on Tuesday [24 May 2022] announced the 1st case of monkeypox detected in the country, reported the state news agency WAM, citing the health ministry. The virus was detected in a 29-year-old woman visiting the Gulf country from West Africa.

Following today's developments, the Ministry of Health and Prevention (MoHAP) has reassured community members that the UAE health authorities were taking all necessary measures, including investigation, examination of contacts, and monitoring their health.

Moreover, the Ministry affirmed that it is cooperating with other health authorities in implementing an epidemiological surveillance system, in accordance with the highest global practices, to ensure sustainable efficiency and community protection from communicable diseases, and rapid detection, as well as work to limit the spread of all diseases and viruses, including monkeypox, in the UAE, it added.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur Mahmoud Orabi

[This case is from West Africa with no apparent relationship to the monkeypox (MPX) outbreak going on in many other parts of the world. One can safely assume that she is infected with the West African clade of MPX virus. - Mod.TY]

******
[10] Morocco: suspected
Date: Tue 24 May 2022
Source: Maroc [edited]
https://www.maroc.ma/en/news/morocco-three-suspected-cases-monkeypox-no-confirmed-cases-ministry


In Morocco, 3 suspected cases of monkeypox have been recorded, but no case has been confirmed so far, the Ministry of Health and Social Protection announced Monday [23 May 2022]. "The 3 suspected cases are in good health, benefiting from the necessary medical supervision," said the coordinator of the National Center for Emergency Public Health Operations of the Ministry of Health, Mouad Mrabet, in a statement to the press.

He stressed that the 3 cases have been submitted to medical analysis pending the results, noting that the health executives have received training on the disease of monkeypox, which has never been detected in the Kingdom.

The Ministry of Health and Social Protection, he said, has established an emergency interaction system in response to the international alert on monkeypox. This system defines the cases of the disease as suspected, probable or confirmed, as well as the procedure to follow for the health protection and treatment of contact cases, he explained.

The establishment of this system comes, said the official, as part of the proactive strategy adopted by the Ministry to address emergency and warning situations related to public health.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur Mahmoud Orabi

[If any or all of these 3 suspected cases are positive, Morocco becomes an additional country to add to the list of those that have cases. The above report does not indicate if the 3 cases acquired the infections, if positive, locally or in another country. - Mod.TY]

